<h3 class="date"><a href="/2009/jun/11/">&#x27a0;</a> June 11, 2009</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="bbc-changes-international-page" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/theeditors/2009/06/change_to_international_pages.html?moduserid=movabletype23_95740&amp;pid=81427036&amp;upm=False&amp;asb=False&amp;pmp=False#dnaacs">BBC - Changes to international pages</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>Genuinely bothersome news from Auntie Beeb.  They&#8217;ve decided to stop letting people outside the US switch to viewing the News site from a UK focus.  That was the whole reason why BBC News has been on my browser toolbar since 1998!  Hoping this will be reversed.</p>

